title: Melbourne Cup Day, New Solar Sharer Scheme, New York City Mayoral Race | 10 News+
description: Australian man Matt Kingston has spoken to 10 News+ about his fearful experience during the UK train stabbing attack which left 11 people injured. It comes amid revelations the suspected stabber may have been on a knife rampage 24 hours before he boarded the London-bound train, and was not stopped by anyone.  There is increasing pressure for Liberal Party leader Sussan Ley to follow the Nationals and ditch their net zero by 2050 target. The party room remains split, with one Ley supporter speaking out and urging the Liberals to remain committed to combatting climate change, in a bid to win back city seats.  Close to a million New Yorkers have already hit the polls on the eve of the city’s mayoral election. A record number of voters are expected to turn out to elect a new man in charge of America’s largest city. The front-runner is 34-year-old Zohran Mamdani, a democratic socialist who could become New York’s first Muslim mayor.  Skywatchers are in for a treat on Wednesday night, with the sky set to be lit up by a rare phenomenon, a full super beaver moon. Dr Matthew Shaw from Swinburne University spoke to 10 News+ about what makes this sight special, and where to get the best views. title: Zohran Mamdani & Andrew Cuomo Face Off In NYC Mayoral Election | 10 News
description: Voters in New York City are taking to the polls to pick their new mayor as front-runner Democrat Zohran Mamdani faces off against former Governor Andrew Cuomo and Republican Curtis Sliwa.  The New York City Board of Elections stated as of 3 pm (local time) nearly 1.5 million people had cast their ballots, with turnout already surpassing the total votes cast in any NYC mayoral election in the past 20 years.  Voters will also pick a new governor in New Jersey and Virginia and decide on a ballot measure in California to redraw its congressional district maps. title: World Reacts As Former US Vice-President Dick Cheney Dies Aged 84 | 10 News
description: Former US vice-president Dick Cheney, one of the most powerful and controversial figures in modern American politics, has died aged 84 from complications of pneumonia and cardiovascular disease.  A key architect of the Iraq War and post-9/11 security agenda, he expanded presidential power, defended interrogation tactics critics labelled torture, and often clashed with senior Bush officials.  Cheney later broke with his party to condemn Donald Trump, warning he posed a threat to US democracy, with Mr Trump yet to comment on his passing.  Reactions have poured in from across the globe, reflecting deep divisions over his legacy and influence.  Praised by George W Bush as a patriot and “among the finest public servants,” he leaves behind a fiercely debated legacy that shaped US foreign policy for decades. title: Miss Universe Contestants Storm Out After Director's Insult | 10 News
description: Dramatic scenes have unfolded at the Miss Universe sashing ceremony in Thailand after a pageant director publicly insulted Miss Mexico for having “no respect” and called her “dumb”.  Vice President for Asia and Oceania of the Miss Universe Organisation Nawat Itsaragrisil openly scolded Fátima Bosch in front of the other contestants for not attending a sponsor shoot earlier that day.  The confrontation was streamed live on the Miss Universe Thailand Facebook page, before contestants staged a mass walkout, including the 2024 Miss Universe winner, Victoria Theilvig, who left the building.  In a statement, the Miss Universe Organisation said, “Together, we are dedicated to upholding the highest standards of respect, safety, and integrity for all participants, staff, and stakeholders.”  Join the conversation and follow us on: TikTok: http://www.tiktok.com/@10NewsAU/ Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/10NewsAU/ Twitter: http://twitter.com/10NewsAU Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/10NewsAU/  10 News airs at 5pm, seven nights a week in your local market on Network 10.
